wikipedia_page.main: George Freeman (27 July 1843 – 18 November 1895) was an English first-class cricketer. He made 32 appearance for Yorkshire County Cricket Club from 1865 to 1880. He also played four matches of first-class cricket for the "United England Eleven" (1866–1869), three games for the "North of England" (1867–1869), four for the "United North of England Eleven" (1870) plus one for the "Players" (1871).
